# JFTL reference test corpus — chunk 8.
# Covers source lines ~1899-2199: the entire module system section (import/
# include/modulemeta, all excluded per agreed policy — JFTL has no module
# concept), a run of error-message try/catch tests, join(",") on mixed
# arrays, the keyword-as-object-key test, division/modulo-by-zero error
# tests, a pow/log2 precision roundtrip, two bare-brace %%FAIL parse-error
# tests, INDEX/JOIN/IN builtin tests, two numbered regression tests, the
# isempty() family, an index("") edge case, builtins-introspection tests,
# and the start of the numeric-literal-precision section. Continues the ID
# sequence (376+) from chunk 7.
#
# Note: source lines 2173-2181 are a block the jq test suite itself has
# commented out with a leading "#" (a disabled/future eval-keyword test,
# marked "uncomment after eval is pushed") — since jq's own suite doesn't
# run these, they're omitted here rather than converted or skip-tagged.
#
# Same caveats as prior chunks: not engine-verified. Two entries below
# (411, 434) depend on internals I can't check without running the engine
# — flagged inline.

