[400-eval]
LEVEL=eval
JQ = {{{
join(",")
}}}
INPUT = {{{
["1",2,true,false,3.4]
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
"1,2,true,false,3.4"
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyeval=','.join(('' if x is None else ('true' if x is True else ('false' if x is False else (x if isinstance(x,str) else __import__('json').dumps(x))))) for x in _)"}
}}}
COMMENT=Reproduces jq's join semantics on mixed types: null becomes "", booleans become lowercase "true"/"false", other non-strings get their canonical JSON form.

[401-eval]
LEVEL=eval
JQ = {{{
.[] | join(",")
}}}
INPUT = {{{
[[], [null], [null,null], [null,null,null]]
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
""
""
","
",,"
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": {"$": true, "foreach": {"in": "$.", "body": {"$pyeval": "','.join(('' if x is None else ('true' if x is True else ('false' if x is False else (x if isinstance(x,str) else __import__('json').dumps(x))))) for x in _)"}}}}
}}}
COMMENT=foreach with no "var" binds each inner array to frame.current ("_" inside the body expression); reuses test 400's join logic per item. Streaming jq's 4 outputs collected into one array.

[402-eval]
LEVEL=eval
JQ = {{{
.[] | join(",")
}}}
INPUT = {{{
