[416-eval]
LEVEL=eval
JQ = {{{
INDEX(range(5)|[., "foo\(.)"]; .[0])
}}}
INPUT = {{{
null
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
{"0":[0,"foo0"],"1":[1,"foo1"],"2":[2,"foo2"],"3":[3,"foo3"],"4":[4,"foo4"]}
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyeval={str(i): [i, 'foo' + str(i)] for i in range(5)}"}
}}}
COMMENT=INDEX(stream; key_expr) builds an object keyed by (stringified) key_expr; reproduced directly as a dict comprehension since the generator and key here are both simple and input-independent.

[417-eval]
LEVEL=eval
JQ = {{{
JOIN({"0":[0,"abc"],"1":[1,"bcd"],"2":[2,"def"],"3":[3,"efg"],"4":[4,"fgh"]}; .[0]|tostring)
}}}
INPUT = {{{
[[5,"foo"],[3,"bar"],[1,"foobar"]]
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
[[[5,"foo"],null],[[3,"bar"],[3,"efg"]],[[1,"foobar"],[1,"bcd"]]]
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyeval=[[x, {'0':[0,'abc'],'1':[1,'bcd'],'2':[2,'def'],'3':[3,'efg'],'4':[4,'fgh']}.get(str(x[0]))] for x in _]"}
}}}
COMMENT=JOIN(table; key_expr) pairs each input item with its lookup in table; the table here is a compile-time constant baked into the source, so it's inlined directly. dict.get returns None (JSON null) on a miss, matching jq's behavior for the [5,"foo"] item.

