[433-py]
LEVEL=py
COMMENT=Tests to cover the new toliteral number functionality (see #1652 and linked issues). We are backward and sanity compatible.
JQ = {{{
map(. == 1)
}}}
INPUT = {{{
[1, 1.0, 1.000, 100e-2, 1e+0, 0.0001e4]
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
[true, true, true, true, true, true]
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$py=[x == 1 for x in _]"}
}}}
COMMENT=All six literals parse to the numeric value 1 once loaded as JSON, so a plain equality comprehension reproduces this without needing eval/run tier.

